<subSubSection lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,535,1734,1793]" box="[151,441,1769,1793]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,260,1769,1793]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Plate 4H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,433,1769,1793]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs. 258–265</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1841,2009]" box="[151,631,1841,1865]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,1841,1865]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.70 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1841,2009]" lastBlockId="36.[151,1436,151,751]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1877,1901]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium size, robust species. General color black and yellow. Forewings with yellow veins on middle of clavus; mesonotum with yellow lateral margins, large yellow spot on each side of middle; pronotum with broken yellow band on anterior margin, small contiguous yellow spots below anterior margin; crown with yellow lateral margins, yellow longitudinal stripe medially; face yellow, broad reddish brown stripe on lateral margins of clypeus and clypellus, black stripe below each eye (
<figureCitation box="[868,972,151,175]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Plate 4H</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, slightly narrower than width of eyes, produced distally about ¼ entire length, lateral margins convergent, slightly carinate, disk elevated, depressed on each side of middle; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum slightly shorter than median length of crown; mesonotum large, about twice as long as median length of pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, narrow, lateral margins broadly convex; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, base inflated, lateral margins constricted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,751]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,367,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view triangulate, small digitate lobe caudoventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1299,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 258</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate long, narrow, few short setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[669,770,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 259</figureCitation>
); style robust, shorter than aedeagus, outer lateral margin broadly expanded and convex in lateral view, small digitate lobe distally (
<figureCitation box="[987,1155,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs. 260, 261</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, tubular, with distinctive long laminate spine subbasally, two narrow spines subapically (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1203,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs. 262, 263</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, membranous on each side of middle, stem very short, broad (
<figureCitation box="[983,1084,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 264</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, strap shape (
<figureCitation box="[237,334,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 265</figureCitation>
), attached to base of aedeagal socle (
<figureCitation box="[748,848,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 258–265" captionStartId="80.[151,258,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,203,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-72@80.[179,1408,191,1810]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 258–265. Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov. (258) male pygofer, lateral view; (259) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (260) right style, lateral view; (261) right style, dorsal view; (262) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (263) aedeagus, dorsal view; (264) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (265) connective, caudal view." pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 262</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
